2026-04-23 | Split Array into Two Equal Sum Subarrays

Question
Return true if such a split exists, else false.
	Approach
1.	Compute total sum of array  
2.	If total sum is odd:
		return false  
3.	Target = totalSum / 2  
4.	Traverse array:
		keep running prefix sum  
5.	If prefix sum == target:
		valid split found → return true  
6.	If never found → return false  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool canSplit(vector<int>& arr) {
        int total = 0;
        for(int x : arr) total += x;
        if(total % 2 != 0) return false;
        int prefix = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < arr.size() - 1; i++){
            prefix += arr[i];
            if(prefix == total / 2)
                return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
};
	Key Insight
We just need to find a point where:
		prefix sum = half of total sum  
This ensures remaining suffix also has equal sum.
